summary:
The Security Council,

Welcoming the 4 September 2017 temporary, bilateral, national ceasefire between the Colombian Government and the National Liberation Army (ELN),

Acknowledging the 29 September 2017 Joint Communiqu√© requesting UN participation as the international component and coordinator of a monitoring and verification mechanism (MVM) to verify compliance with the ceasefire,

Recalling the UN Mission in Colombia's positive role in monitoring and verifying the ceasefire between the Colombian Government and the FARC-EP,

1. Welcomes the Secretary-General's 2 October 2017 letter;

2. Decides the UN Verification Mission shall, until 9 January 2018, participate in and coordinate the MVM to: 
    (i) Verify compliance with the ELN ceasefire;
    (ii) Prevent incidents through enhanced coordination;
    (iii) Enable timely response to incidents;
    (iv) Verify and report publicly on compliance;

3. Approves the Secretary-General's recommendations, including adding up to 70 international observers, using existing resources without affecting previous tasks;

4. Welcomes the proposal to incorporate ceasefire verification reporting within the existing cycle and requests an update by 8 December 2017.
